@startuml
skinparam maxMessageSize 150
actor Client
participant "FastAPI App" as API
participant "Google OAuth2" as Google
database "Database" as DB

== Authentication Flow (Google) ==
Client -> Google: 1. Request OAuth2 ID Token\n(from frontend)
Google --> Client: 2. Return ID Token

Client -> API: 3. POST /auth/login\n(with ID Token)
activate API
API -> Google: 4. Verify ID Token (using verify_oauth2_token)
Google --> API: 5. Verification Result & User Info (Email, Name)

alt If Token Valid
    API -> DB: 6. Check if user exists by Email
    DB --> API: 7. User Result

    alt User does not exist
        API -> DB: 8. Auto-provision new User
        DB --> API: 9. User Created
    end

    API -> API: 10. Generate JWT Access Token\n(signed with SECRET_KEY)
    API --> Client: 11. Return {"access_token": "...", "token_type": "bearer"}
else If Token Invalid
    API --> Client: 11b. 400 Bad Request
end
deactivate API

== Protected Route Access ==
Client -> API: 12. GET /protected/route\n(Header: Authorization: Bearer <JWT>)
activate API
API -> API: 13. Decode & Verify JWT signature
API -> DB: 14. Fetch User by ID from JWT payload
DB --> API: 15. User Object

alt If Token valid & User exists
    API --> Client: 16. Return requested data
else
    API --> Client: 16b. 401 Unauthorized
end
deactivate API

@enduml
